### Bank & Payment System API Tests
### Use with IntelliJ IDEA HTTP Client or REST Client extension in VSCode

### Variables
@bankHost = http://localhost:8080
@paymentHost = http://localhost:8081

################################################################################
### BANK SERVICE TESTS
################################################################################

### 1. Create Account for User 1
POST {{bankHost}}/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "accountType": "CHECKING"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("accountId", response.body.id);
    client.log("Account created with ID: " + response.body.id);
%}

### 2. Deposit 100,000 KRW
POST {{bankHost}}/api/accounts/{{accountId}}/deposit
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: deposit-{{$timestamp}}

{
  "amount": 100000,
  "description": "Initial deposit"
}

### 3. Check Balance (should be 100,000)
GET {{bankHost}}/api/accounts/{{accountId}}/balance

### 4. Get Transaction History
GET {{bankHost}}/api/accounts/{{accountId}}/transactions?page=0&size=10

################################################################################
### PAYMENT SERVICE TESTS
################################################################################

### 5. Payment Approval - 30,000 KRW
POST {{paymentHost}}/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: payment-{{$timestamp}}

{
  "userId": "user-001",
  "accountId": {{accountId}},
  "amount": 30000,
  "merchantId": "MERCHANT-001",
  "orderId": "ORDER-{{$timestamp}}",
  "description": "Product purchase"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("paymentId", response.body.paymentId);
    client.log("Payment created with ID: " + response.body.paymentId);
%}

### 6. Check Balance After Payment (should be 70,000)
GET {{bankHost}}/api/accounts/{{accountId}}/balance

### 7. Get Payment Details
GET {{paymentHost}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}

### 8. Partial Cancel - 10,000 KRW
POST {{paymentHost}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}/cancel
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: cancel-{{$timestamp}}

{
  "amount": 10000,
  "reason": "Customer request - partial refund"
}

### 9. Check Balance After Cancel (should be 80,000)
GET {{bankHost}}/api/accounts/{{accountId}}/balance

### 10. Another Partial Cancel - 5,000 KRW
POST {{paymentHost}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}/cancel
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: cancel-2-{{$timestamp}}

{
  "amount": 5000,
  "reason": "Additional refund"
}

### 11. Final Balance Check (should be 85,000)
GET {{bankHost}}/api/accounts/{{accountId}}/balance

### 12. Final Payment Status
GET {{paymentHost}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}

################################################################################
### ERROR SCENARIOS
################################################################################

### Test: Insufficient Balance - Try to withdraw 200,000 KRW
POST {{bankHost}}/api/accounts/{{accountId}}/withdraw
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: withdraw-fail-{{$timestamp}}

{
  "amount": 200000,
  "description": "Should fail - insufficient balance"
}

### Test: Cancel More Than Approved Amount
POST {{paymentHost}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}/cancel
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: cancel-fail-{{$timestamp}}

{
  "amount": 50000,
  "reason": "Should fail - exceeds approved amount"
}

### Test: Missing Idempotency Key
POST {{bankHost}}/api/accounts/{{accountId}}/deposit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 1000,
  "description": "Should fail - no idempotency key"
}

### Test: Non-existent Payment
GET {{paymentHost}}/api/payments/NON-EXISTENT-ID

################################################################################
### MONITORING
################################################################################

### Health Check - Bank Service
GET {{bankHost}}/actuator/health

### Health Check - Payment Service
GET {{paymentHost}}/actuator/health

### Prometheus Metrics - Bank Service
GET {{bankHost}}/actuator/prometheus

### Prometheus Metrics - Payment Service
GET {{paymentHost}}/actuator/prometheus
